00:05:19.020 --> 00:05:20.800
but 2000 or 2001.

00:05:21.210 --> 00:05:26.800
That was the first data services
offering that has been popular.

00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:31.440
And during the time that
European couriers were

00:05:31.540 --> 00:05:36.550
struggling with the web services,
Docomo was doing very,

00:05:36.740 --> 00:05:37.800
very well in Japan.

00:05:37.860 --> 00:05:44.270
And they have now tens of millions
of subscribers in Japan only.

00:05:44.990 --> 00:05:51.400
So iMode services have expanded overseas.

00:05:51.400 --> 00:05:57.540
They've been rolled out by nine couriers
around the world and outside Japan.

00:05:57.670 --> 00:06:02.180
And more couriers are joining every year.

00:06:02.300 --> 00:06:07.040
And all these couriers formed
a group called the Alliance.

00:06:07.250 --> 00:06:14.040
Which aim is to specify and to
maybe adjust the iMode systems to

00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:18.070
adapt it to their local markets.

00:06:19.590 --> 00:06:24.150
iMode is based mainly on the clear
separation of the roles between

00:06:24.470 --> 00:06:27.690
content providers and carriers.

00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:33.030
The point we want to be clear on is
that we are not a content provider.

00:06:33.030 --> 00:06:36.790
We don't want to provide our
customers our own content.

00:06:36.790 --> 00:06:37.440
We can't do it.

00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:39.510
It's not our job.

00:06:40.020 --> 00:06:44.450
And iMOD relies on standard
technologies that we like:

00:06:44.660 --> 00:06:47.380
HTML, email.

00:06:47.380 --> 00:06:57.110
So no MMS,
no telecom originated standards.

00:07:00.130 --> 00:07:04.510
A few words about the iMode ecosystem,
why iMode is pretty

00:07:04.510 --> 00:07:08.160
well working in Europe.

00:07:08.330 --> 00:07:11.500
The customer is of course
center of the place,

00:07:11.630 --> 00:07:13.400
the central role.

00:07:13.400 --> 00:07:17.890
And we as a courier, we

00:07:18.160 --> 00:07:22.050
Allow the content providers to
distribute their contents to the

00:07:22.210 --> 00:07:24.490
end users through our network.

00:07:24.550 --> 00:07:26.890
That's just what we do.

00:07:26.970 --> 00:07:28.790
We don't do any content creation.

00:07:28.940 --> 00:07:35.370
We don't host any content
providers or we don't host any of

00:07:35.450 --> 00:07:38.190
our own content on our servers.

00:07:39.190 --> 00:07:45.870
It's really,
we are offering a pipe for people to web,

00:07:45.870 --> 00:07:49.090
to browse iMode sites.

00:07:49.150 --> 00:07:50.090
That's all.

00:07:50.350 --> 00:07:54.510
But we are trying to do it our best.

00:07:54.720 --> 00:08:01.320
One thing where we are pretty good at
and where we are trying to help our

00:08:01.320 --> 00:08:06.850
content providers is that we have a
unique relationship to our customers.

00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:11.960
Our customers get a bill from us, by us,
each month,

00:08:11.990 --> 00:08:21.470
so they know who their carrier is
and at this point we have also a huge

00:08:21.760 --> 00:08:25.690
Customer Care and
Customer Relationship Department.

00:08:25.690 --> 00:08:27.700
So that's one of our strengths.

00:08:27.790 --> 00:08:31.160
And we want to allow
the content providers,

00:08:31.160 --> 00:08:37.050
big ones or small ones,
to benefit from this.

00:08:37.700 --> 00:08:54.900
[Transcript missing]

00:08:55.310 --> 00:08:56.820
The iMOD model is pretty clear.

00:08:56.820 --> 00:09:02.080
We share the content providers
get 86% of the subscription fees.

00:09:02.190 --> 00:09:07.420
So a typical subscription fee is about
between one and three euro a month.

00:09:07.550 --> 00:09:12.190
So if you want to get weather
for your location in France,

00:09:12.240 --> 00:09:17.920
then you would pay one euro a month
to a weather content provider.

00:09:17.990 --> 00:09:20.230
So that's pretty fair.

00:09:20.530 --> 00:09:25.180
And we pay back 86% of this one
euro to the content providers.

00:09:25.200 --> 00:09:32.190
And we keep the money
for the packet traffic.

00:09:37.640 --> 00:09:44.160
So the key for success of our
iMode services is that through

00:09:44.160 --> 00:09:48.620
iMode we have the ability to
specify and to adjust handset

00:09:48.620 --> 00:09:52.500
specifications to our local market.

00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:58.930
That's something that our
competitors are beginning to do.

00:09:58.990 --> 00:10:05.970
For example,
you see Vodafone is working more and more

00:10:05.970 --> 00:10:09.940
closely with their handset providers,
which give them the

00:10:09.940 --> 00:10:13.760
ability to do so as well,
to control the handsets,

00:10:13.950 --> 00:10:18.150
control the features, and to specify,
for example,

00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:21.080
the file formats they want to use.

00:10:21.920 --> 00:10:28.240
It guarantees for the end users,
it guarantees a consistent

00:10:28.240 --> 00:10:32.230
experience throughout,
across all the handsets

00:10:32.290 --> 00:10:35.800
that they could buy from us.

00:10:35.800 --> 00:10:41.320
So you get for example on each iMode
handset you have a hard key which is

00:10:41.350 --> 00:10:45.800
always the same place on the handset
and you'll find it on any iMode handset.

00:10:45.800 --> 00:10:53.700
So if I change my handset, if I upgrade,
I'll still find the same navigation menu,

00:10:54.260 --> 00:10:55.800
always the same ergonomics.

00:10:55.800 --> 00:10:58.800
So we want to keep it
simple for end users.

00:10:58.960 --> 00:11:06.800
And most of them don't have PCs at home
so that's maybe their unique data device.

00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:11.960
So we really want to make it a very
simple experience so that they can enter

00:11:11.960 --> 00:11:14.770
the data world as easily as possible.

00:11:14.800 --> 00:11:15.800
Thank you.

00:11:19.390 --> 00:11:25.310
Something very important for
our content providers is that we

00:11:25.470 --> 00:11:30.300
guarantee the content providers
that their content will look exactly

00:11:30.300 --> 00:11:32.300
the same across all our handsets.

00:11:32.300 --> 00:11:37.300
I was discussing this with Alec
from MTV right before the session.

00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:41.960
If MTV gives us a picture,
then we guarantee them that the

00:11:41.960 --> 00:11:47.600
same picture will look exactly the
same on our latest handsets and on

00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:51.290
the handset that we launched two
years ago when we launched iMode.

00:11:51.300 --> 00:11:57.300
So that's a burden that the content
providers don't have to take care of.

00:11:57.300 --> 00:12:03.300
And they pretty much appreciate
the homogeneity of iMode handsets.

00:12:03.300 --> 00:12:07.300
That, of course, reduces drastically the
content productivity.

00:12:07.300 --> 00:12:11.490
It reduces the production costs for them
so they can concentrate on their job,

00:12:11.550 --> 00:12:14.300
which is mainly produce content.

00:12:14.300 --> 00:12:21.260
And that's building the
success for our data services.

00:12:21.300 --> 00:12:26.940
One word about the content providers.

00:12:28.710 --> 00:12:32.260
Copyright Control Management:
iMode has a very simple but very

00:12:32.260 --> 00:12:37.700
efficient feature which allows a
content provider to protect its content.

00:12:37.700 --> 00:12:42.680
And we ensure the content provider that
the content won't go out of the phone.

00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:44.690
It's stuck.

00:12:44.700 --> 00:12:46.690
As soon as you download a picture,
for example,

00:12:46.700 --> 00:12:51.390
and the content provider protects it,
then you won't be able to take it

00:12:51.390 --> 00:12:54.680
out through infrared or Bluetooth.

