00:17:31.400 --> 00:17:36.950
The first network is GSM with
very limited data support.

00:17:37.020 --> 00:17:39.780
It evolves to GPRS.

00:17:40.010 --> 00:17:45.350
That's what we've deployed and now we
are There are two after GPRS deployment.

00:17:45.350 --> 00:17:50.020
There are two alternatives You can
go either for a network upgrade and

00:17:50.020 --> 00:17:56.090
go for edge or you can go for whole
completely new network that is UMTS

00:17:59.670 --> 00:18:05.740
So you have two options,
Edge versus UMTS or 3G.

00:18:07.600 --> 00:18:18.100
So to have a better throughput
than with the current GPRS network,

00:18:18.100 --> 00:18:21.700
you have to deploy one
of these two networks.

00:18:21.960 --> 00:18:31.280
UMTS networks offer very high capacity,
pretty high speeds, but there's a but.

00:18:31.580 --> 00:18:38.010
They assume a huge upfront deployment
cost because it's a brand new network.

00:18:38.130 --> 00:18:40.890
You have to deploy
your network from zero.

00:18:40.980 --> 00:18:43.880
You can't just upgrade your radio sites.

00:18:43.900 --> 00:18:50.050
You have to make new radio sites and you
have to build new hardware on top of it.

00:18:53.070 --> 00:18:56.940
To give you an idea,
if we are to deploy a 3G

00:18:56.940 --> 00:19:04.580
UMTS network in France,
we have to pay 6 billion euros,

00:19:04.580 --> 00:19:04.580
6 billion.

00:19:05.400 --> 00:19:09.160
A bit more than six
billion dollars for it.

00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:17.160
That's exactly what our GSM,
the whole GSM network cost to us about

00:19:17.160 --> 00:19:20.200
six years ago when we deployed it.

00:19:20.320 --> 00:19:29.200
So that's something that's
still very money demanding.

00:19:29.620 --> 00:19:35.230
The problem is with,
if you go today for a 3G deployment,

00:19:35.230 --> 00:19:37.300
you have very few,

00:19:37.300 --> 00:21:13.000
[Transcript missing]

00:21:13.620 --> 00:21:18.210
That's something that might
make a huge difference in the

00:21:18.380 --> 00:21:22.830
first years of UMTS deployment
between us and our competitors.

00:21:22.830 --> 00:21:24.760
That's our strength.

00:21:26.720 --> 00:21:35.390
So, of course, UMTS is an option for us,
but in a few years from now,

00:21:35.390 --> 00:21:41.310
we expect to increase our revenues
first using the edge network,

00:21:41.310 --> 00:21:50.370
and then we'll think again what
we'll be doing for a UMTS deployment.

